17:12.591 --> 17:13.472
That's all he's saying.

17:14.113 --> 17:15.394
We all have different cultures.

17:15.775 --> 17:17.617
Thank God we're not all the same culture.

17:20.360 --> 17:22.503
Because to me, cultures are intriguing.

17:24.325 --> 17:26.407
I like the different aspects of different cultures.

17:28.169 --> 17:29.010
It's not talking about that.

17:29.030 --> 17:32.274
It says we have one common goal that we will protect our land.

17:33.634 --> 17:34.776
We will believe in this country.

17:36.799 --> 17:39.202
We will stand for what's right according to the Word of God.

17:40.584 --> 17:55.226
And I only threw that in there so we could see anyone coming from outside of Israel, especially pagan nation like the Canaanites, which Rahab was, had to separate from their former identity with the Lord and His people.

17:55.927 --> 18:03.058
This was both a spiritual and a covenant, oh man, covenantal, covenantal.

18:03.810 --> 18:04.531
transition.

18:05.132 --> 18:13.223
Eventually, she was brought in because of this, because she became part of them.

18:14.725 --> 18:18.710
She was spared, but she was not just spared.

18:19.311 --> 18:20.032
She was brought in.

18:20.172 --> 18:21.313
She became family.

18:22.215 --> 18:27.181
She went from outsider to insider, from rejected to redeemed.

18:27.782 --> 18:30.225
And then the Bible tells us something that should amaze all of us.

18:30.245 --> 18:33.810
This is really amazing if you understand the story.

18:34.722 --> 18:40.849
Matthew 1, 5, Salmon was the father of Boaz, whose mother was Rahab.

18:41.630 --> 18:45.075
Boaz was the father of Obed, whose mother was Ruth.

18:45.675 --> 18:50.561
Obed was the father of Jesse, who was the father of David, and in the line of Jesus.

18:50.902 --> 18:54.807
God takes a prostitute.

18:54.827 --> 19:01.375
She becomes part of them, and God puts her in the lineage of Jesus.

19:03.257 --> 19:04.178
Isn't that crazy?

19:04.642 --> 19:07.185
And I don't know about you, but it blows me away.

19:07.245 --> 19:10.188
See, Rahab became part of the lineage of Jesus Christ.

19:10.208 --> 19:11.289
Think about it just for a moment.

19:11.590 --> 19:17.977
The prostitute from Jericho became part of the family line of the Savior of the world.

19:18.037 --> 19:18.337
Why?

19:18.557 --> 19:24.083
Because God takes the unlikely and builds them and gives them hope and saves their life.

19:26.646 --> 19:28.228
And this is how we should live.

19:29.209 --> 19:30.751
There's a guy in Clovis named Wally.

19:30.771 --> 19:31.532
He may be watching.

19:32.152 --> 19:33.714
He usually goes to both services.

19:34.722 --> 19:36.104
And I asked him if I could do some of this.

19:36.144 --> 19:36.985
He said, absolutely.

19:38.086 --> 19:40.048
He was in prison for 17 years.

19:41.229 --> 19:43.912
I think he was called, considered one of the OGs in prison.

19:43.932 --> 19:46.755
I think he ran one of the whole gangs.

19:46.775 --> 19:49.198
He escaped from prison two different times.

19:50.139 --> 19:51.721
So he's pretty interesting, crafty.

19:54.784 --> 19:58.969
And somehow in all that he accepts Jesus as his Lord and Savior.

20:00.771 --> 20:02.493
When he goes back into prison, they catch him.

20:02.553 --> 20:03.634
He goes back in.

20:03.714 --> 20:06.517
I guess all of his boys were like, come on, what are we going to do now?

20:06.537 --> 20:07.378
What's the plan?

20:07.919 --> 20:16.488
I guess he jumped up on a table, started yelling at him, using a lot of words, just saved.

20:16.508 --> 20:17.209
Come on, somebody.

20:18.190 --> 20:20.152
He was just saved.

20:20.172 --> 20:23.916
And so he used the words, I'm not doing this blankety blank stuff.

20:23.976 --> 20:24.957
You're not going to do this.

20:24.977 --> 20:26.018
And he starts getting on him.

20:26.038 --> 20:27.340
And so they were afraid of him.

20:27.360 --> 20:28.301
So they just let him be.

20:29.842 --> 20:30.723
He gets out of prison.

20:31.584 --> 20:33.266
Mary's a wonderful lady named Stella.

20:36.578 --> 20:37.880
And God blesses his life.

20:39.002 --> 20:40.404
He owns an electric business.

20:41.966 --> 20:43.469
He's got some great contracts.

20:43.989 --> 20:44.871
And can I say this?

20:45.332 --> 20:49.198
Him and his wife are two of the most generous people in this whole church.

20:50.700 --> 20:53.104
He's so grateful for what God did to his life.

20:54.205 --> 20:57.851
He was that unlikely guy that you don't know what everything, how could he be saved?

20:57.871 --> 20:58.913
How could he serve God?

20:59.453 --> 21:00.595
That's what religion says.

21:00.896 --> 21:02.418
You know what God's people say?

21:02.594 --> 21:03.014
You know what?

21:03.074 --> 21:03.875
There's hope in them.

21:04.055 --> 21:05.116
There's potential in them.

21:05.136 --> 21:06.798
There's something we cannot see.

21:08.079 --> 21:12.263
When the prophet went to the house of Jesse to anoint the kids, one of the sons is king.

21:12.563 --> 21:15.847
The first one came, the oldest, sharp, big, strong.

21:16.227 --> 21:19.490
And the prophet said, surely this is the king of Israel.

21:19.550 --> 21:20.691
God said, nope.

21:22.273 --> 21:23.113
We'll bring the next one.

21:23.374 --> 21:24.395
Surely this is him.

21:24.675 --> 21:25.756
Nope.

21:25.776 --> 21:26.677
Goes through all of them.

21:26.717 --> 21:29.319
And finally he's like, Jesse, do you have any more kids?

21:29.359 --> 21:31.161
I got a teenager out there, 10 in the sheep.

21:31.361 --> 21:32.242
He said, bring him in.

21:33.698 --> 21:36.201
As soon as the Prophet saw him, God said, that's my man.

21:37.262 --> 21:37.783
A kid.

21:39.685 --> 21:42.128
And David anointed him as king, then God said something very interesting.

21:42.529 --> 21:43.810
Man looks to the outside.

21:44.251 --> 21:45.572
God always looks to the inside.

21:47.875 --> 21:52.701
That's why this is so intriguing to me.

21:52.741 --> 21:57.126
It's just how God sees people and what he does for people.

22:00.851 --> 22:02.152
God did not just save her.

22:02.252 --> 22:03.634
He God honored her.

22:04.962 --> 22:07.545
God did not just rescue her, God restored her.

22:08.927 --> 22:10.028
That is what grace does.

22:10.128 --> 22:12.170
Grace does not just forgive your past.

22:12.190 --> 22:13.031
I love this statement.

22:13.412 --> 22:14.773
Grace gives you a future.

22:15.975 --> 22:18.197
Grace does not just rescue you from something.

22:18.578 --> 22:20.340
Grace brings you into something.

22:20.740 --> 22:25.686
Rahab prepares us for Jesus because Jesus came for outsiders.

22:26.287 --> 22:27.588
Jesus came for sinners.

22:28.029 --> 22:29.971
Jesus came for broken people.

22:30.411 --> 22:32.594
Jesus came behind enemy walls.

22:32.770 --> 22:40.719
and his cross became our scarlet cord, his blood became our covering, his sacrifice became our salvation.

22:41.040 --> 22:42.522
So what does this mean for us?

22:42.642 --> 22:45.946
First, it means you are not too far gone.

22:46.867 --> 22:49.109
If God can save Rahab, he can save you.

22:50.030 --> 22:59.922
There is no past who broken, no life too messy, no person too far away that grace can reach further than we think.

23:02.978 --> 23:05.782
Second, it means God uses unlikely people.

23:06.503 --> 23:08.406
Some of you think God could never use you.

23:09.368 --> 23:10.930
I hear it all the time.

23:10.950 --> 23:12.032
I don't know how God could use me.

23:12.633 --> 23:13.534
I'm not worthy enough.

23:13.774 --> 23:14.275
Sure, you're not.

23:14.976 --> 23:16.879
But he can make you worthy by his grace.

23:18.001 --> 23:19.103
None of us are worthy enough.

23:23.209 --> 23:26.293
But God specializes in using unlikely people.

23:27.195 --> 23:28.076
He used Rahab.

23:28.917 --> 23:29.739
He used David.

23:30.800 --> 23:31.922
He used Peter.

23:32.834 --> 23:36.438
He used Paul and he will use you.

23:37.660 --> 23:40.103
He said, but Paul wrote two thirds of New Testament.

23:40.363 --> 23:43.167
But before that, Paul killed Christians.

23:43.367 --> 23:44.688
He separated families.

23:44.929 --> 23:46.491
He put them in slavery.

23:46.811 --> 23:49.174
He probably put them in the lines then to be killed.

23:50.996 --> 23:52.438
He destroyed families.

23:53.860 --> 23:56.223
And so no one would ever think, oh man, God's gonna save him.

23:56.263 --> 23:57.544
He's gonna be used in a great way.

23:57.744 --> 23:57.905
Uh-uh.

24:00.388 --> 24:02.290
But God made him on the road to Damascus.

24:03.138 --> 24:06.003
And said, Paul, why are you kicking against the goats, dude?

24:06.984 --> 24:08.607
You can't win this battle.

24:11.171 --> 24:12.073
It changed his life.

24:14.196 --> 24:18.203
He suffered no doubt, but he made a lot of other people suffer.

24:18.964 --> 24:22.369
But God used him in a mighty way that he's still changing lives today.

24:23.952 --> 24:30.162
God used him if I was obedient, and he wrote what God wanted us to hear, that's why you have to believe in the Bible.

24:31.330 --> 24:33.513
Well, I believe in parts of it, then you don't believe it at all.

24:35.416 --> 24:38.640
You know, I go to, I love golden corral, I love Taco Bell.

24:40.082 --> 24:42.005
I can eat at one of those places every day.

24:43.707 --> 24:46.611
People think I'm kidding, I'm so fancy, that's my place.

24:48.293 --> 24:51.458
And when I go to go to corral, you know, there's a big buffet.

24:52.059 --> 24:57.025
I get the exact same thing every time, and this has been going on 10 or 15 years.

24:58.427 --> 25:00.370
I walk in, I get the bourbon chicken.

25:01.538 --> 25:03.281
I get mashed potatoes and gravy.

25:03.321 --> 25:04.803
I get a piece of fried chicken.

25:05.364 --> 25:06.565
I get green beans.

25:06.686 --> 25:07.527
I get a roll.

25:07.867 --> 25:09.510
And then for dessert, I get the same thing.

25:09.590 --> 25:12.154
I get the piece of the chocolate cake and blueberry pie.

25:12.454 --> 25:15.439
The exact same menu every time I go in there.

25:16.861 --> 25:19.565
And you know what that's, you know, you say, why are you telling us that?

25:19.645 --> 25:20.526
Because here's the thing.

25:20.827 --> 25:22.269
That's how some people treat the word.

25:22.629 --> 25:24.572
I like this, I like that.

25:24.733 --> 25:27.196
I don't like this other style.

25:27.216 --> 25:27.897
I don't want that.

25:28.759 --> 25:31.122
But unless you believe the whole thing, you can't believe it at all.

25:31.906 --> 25:35.531
Unless you believe it from Genesis to Revelation, you can't believe it, folks.

25:36.151 --> 25:38.354
It is not a buffet to pick and choose.

25:41.158 --> 25:42.560
Dang, that was free, too.

25:46.084 --> 25:47.706
So if we use all of them, he'll use you.

25:48.427 --> 25:52.753
Third, it means we must be the kind of church that makes room for the unlikely.

25:54.054 --> 25:56.978
We are not here to build a country club of perfect people.

25:57.634 --> 26:02.120
There's so many people I talk to who said, yeah, I go to this church, because this person goes there, that person goes there, that person goes there.

26:02.380 --> 26:03.562
I'm like, so what?

26:05.444 --> 26:06.906
Because they look the part.

26:07.867 --> 26:10.591
Or they want to be, you know, rub elbows with certain kinds of people.

26:10.831 --> 26:14.176
Can I tell you, I've rubbed elbows with every kind of person in this state.

26:14.616 --> 26:17.040
And most of them, I don't want to ever rub an elbow again.

26:17.060 --> 26:21.145
In fact, they start rubbing like, dude, you better back up, man.

26:21.806 --> 26:25.010
I'm gonna grab Bubba and Guido, and we're gonna take care of this right now.

26:26.594 --> 26:28.176
It's just a facade.

26:29.077 --> 26:30.359
Well, I just want to be around those people.

26:30.379 --> 26:31.260
I want to meet those people.

26:31.280 --> 26:32.501
Guys, let me tell you something.

26:32.902 --> 26:34.344
Or I want my family to be like them.

26:34.384 --> 26:34.964
Be careful.

26:35.986 --> 26:38.249
Because I know people said, man, I like my family like that.

26:38.269 --> 26:41.873
And I'm like, no, no, no, you don't.

26:42.995 --> 26:51.085
We won't tell them why, but just say, no, you know, you want your family to be like what God is using you and your family.

26:51.105 --> 26:52.586
And there's no two families the same.

26:52.647 --> 26:53.908
We all have our weirdness.

26:55.010 --> 26:55.410
Come on.

26:56.194 --> 26:59.860
We all have our dysfunction, and then we have our good stuff.

27:00.681 --> 27:04.947
I mean, we may love our family, but, you know, there's those people like, oh, dang, yeah, here they come.

27:06.390 --> 27:07.391
Here comes Uncle Bob.

27:07.471 --> 27:08.513
He'll talk to Uncle Bob.

27:08.553 --> 27:09.314
Bob's crazy.

27:12.319 --> 27:17.446
But we are not to build a club for so-called perfect people.

27:18.368 --> 27:25.138
We are here to build a place where broken people can find grace, because that

27:25.378 --> 27:27.121
is who Jesus came for.

27:27.982 --> 27:31.167
And finally it means salvation is found in Jesus alone.

27:31.828 --> 27:33.290
He is our scarlet cord.

27:33.330 --> 27:35.173
He is our covering.

27:35.593 --> 27:37.096
He is our salvation.

27:37.676 --> 27:40.481
Out of nowhere, grace showed up behind enemy walls.

27:41.142 --> 27:43.084
Out of nowhere, God saved Rahab.

27:43.485 --> 27:46.049
Out of nowhere, God brought her into his family.

27:46.389 --> 27:51.357
And the same grace that found Rahab is still reaching for people today.

27:51.397 --> 27:54.802
It is reaching for people who feel unqualified.

27:55.682 --> 27:57.465
It is reaching for people who feel unworthy.

27:58.286 --> 28:00.249
It is reaching for people who feel forgotten.

28:01.631 --> 28:03.094
And folks, I'd be one of those kids.

28:04.055 --> 28:07.681
When I got to say, I'd be one of those people that, why would you use him?

28:07.701 --> 28:11.787
I was just happy to get my diploma from Clovis High School.

28:11.847 --> 28:14.792
I felt like I put one over on him like, they gave me this like way.

28:18.338 --> 28:19.720
But God sees what's in you.

28:21.202 --> 28:23.666
When you come under his grace and mercy,

28:23.842 --> 28:28.769
and you receive the gift of salvation, he can bring out what's really in you.

28:29.270 --> 28:33.255
He can help heal all the brokenness from your life and your past.

28:34.017 --> 28:36.260
That's what the church of the Lord Jesus Christ does.

28:36.780 --> 28:40.025
We reach one more person, the most unlikely.

28:40.946 --> 28:43.610
I mean, there's people in here that would never think you're in here to serve in God.

28:43.810 --> 28:46.655
You probably looked at church years ago and said, I'll never be one of them.

28:47.295 --> 28:48.237
And now you're one of them.

28:51.501 --> 28:51.922
Why?

28:52.450 --> 28:54.813
Because what God did in you, He sees you.

28:55.014 --> 28:55.915
He sees in you.

28:57.617 --> 29:04.727
He sees what's in, He knows the gifts and callings that are within you for you to do incredible things in your life if you want to.

29:05.308 --> 29:06.289
But you got to believe Him.

29:06.309 --> 29:07.371
You got to do what He asked.

29:07.651 --> 29:13.359
You got to, when I was talking about Brother Wally, He's one of the most giving guys I know ever.

29:14.160 --> 29:16.083
And I say, man, you're doing too much.

29:16.163 --> 29:19.187
And He goes, no, man, what God did for me, I'm never doing too much.

29:19.628 --> 29:21.170
You got to stay grateful.

29:21.634 --> 29:23.056
And that's how you stay grateful.

29:23.416 --> 29:28.121
Instead of whining and complaining to God, say, God, this is hard, but I'm grateful you saved my life.

29:28.361 --> 29:31.905
God, this is hard, but I'm glad you believe in me when no one else believed in me.

29:32.185 --> 29:35.429
God, I'm glad you've never rejected me like other people reject me.

29:36.090 --> 29:37.091
You don't abandon me.

29:37.591 --> 29:38.813
You don't disregard me.

29:40.755 --> 29:42.056
And that's the goodness of God.

29:42.076 --> 29:46.181
We got to stay appreciative to him because God is the God of people.

29:46.501 --> 29:47.922
And he wants anybody.

29:47.943 --> 29:51.186
He'll take anybody that's willing to come into his family.

29:51.618 --> 29:53.400
And that's what we need to understand.

29:56.384 --> 29:58.567
So it is reaching for people who feel unqualified.

29:58.587 --> 30:00.189
It's reaching for people who feel unworthy.

30:00.930 --> 30:02.833
It is reaching for people who feel forgotten.

30:03.574 --> 30:07.659
Because salvation has always been wider than we think.

30:08.681 --> 30:10.083
Grace is still saving.

30:10.804 --> 30:12.045
Grace is still reaching.

30:12.666 --> 30:16.952
Grace is still building God's family out of nowhere.

30:17.533 --> 30:18.674
God will show up in your life.

30:19.330 --> 30:21.734
Father in Jesus' name, I thank you for your words, it's truth.

30:22.194 --> 30:23.917
Thank you for your help and our time of need.

30:24.418 --> 30:28.063
I thank you, God, for your wisdom, your love and your direction.

30:28.604 --> 30:29.606
And Father, I pray.

30:30.787 --> 30:38.299
Father, when I said I like this sermon, I think it just resonates with where I've come from and how I've thought.

30:39.541 --> 30:45.810
And God, I'm praying today with all my heart that you,

30:47.138 --> 30:51.062
would touch people's hearts and minds in this place and let them know.

30:51.102 --> 30:53.464
They can never become worthy enough.

30:53.524 --> 30:54.725
They can't fix their lives.

30:54.745 --> 30:55.706
They can't clean it up.

30:56.047 --> 31:01.832
They just have to humble themselves and come to you and say, God, I receive Jesus as my Lord and Savior.

31:02.433 --> 31:03.974
And then Lord, you'll go to work in them.

31:04.314 --> 31:04.975
You'll help them.

31:04.995 --> 31:05.776
You'll forgive them.

31:05.796 --> 31:06.577
You'll bless them.

31:10.280 --> 31:16.306
Because God only, you know what we can become if we truly put our life in your hands.

31:17.026 --> 31:19.128
You're the potter and we're the clay you moved us.

31:20.370 --> 31:23.393
It's one day at a time, one moment at a time, one step at a time.

31:24.294 --> 31:26.096
And God, there'll be bad moments in our life.

31:26.136 --> 31:29.299
We'll still have those where we, oh man, I shouldn't have did that.

31:29.319 --> 31:34.926
But God, thank you for your grace and mercy that we can come and repent and get our lives right.

31:35.606 --> 31:36.487
Ask for forgiveness.

31:37.468 --> 31:41.793
And you'll always forgive us because you are the God of another chance.

31:42.874 --> 31:44.396
So bless each one in here, God.

31:45.217 --> 31:46.418
May they walk out of here.

31:46.850 --> 31:48.873
with a different thought, a different process.

31:50.695 --> 31:55.141
May they walk out of here thinking different than they came in in a good way.

31:55.962 --> 31:59.186
They said, okay, God can't use me, I am somebody.

32:00.288 --> 32:08.378
Maybe I'm one of the unlikely, maybe you're one of the perfect kind of people, but not perfect people go to heaven, save people go to heaven.

32:09.059 --> 32:14.386
Not people who just look good, you can't be pretty and handsome and go to heaven, you must be saved.

32:15.394 --> 32:17.057
And we all have to come the same way.

32:17.477 --> 32:22.966
We have to humble our hearts and minds before God and say, God, come into my life.

32:24.008 --> 32:27.293
Be Lord of my life in Jesus' name.

32:27.393 --> 32:31.940
So if that's you and you say, preacher, pastor Steve, I walk with God, but I walked away.

32:32.962 --> 32:33.843
I want to come home now.

32:36.287 --> 32:36.908
I want to come home.

32:40.694 --> 32:42.096
And you can say, well, I did all these things.

32:42.116 --> 32:43.218
It doesn't matter what you did.

32:44.034 --> 32:45.376
It matters what you're doing today.

32:46.737 --> 32:48.600
And God will forgive you if you want him to.

32:48.620 --> 32:51.183
If you ask him to, he will.

32:51.203 --> 32:53.325
Over here and you've never asked Jesus to be Lord of your life.

32:54.046 --> 33:02.737
Maybe you're living the lie that I belong to this church and I got, you know, Christen in this church and I got dedicated in that church.

33:02.757 --> 33:06.922
I got confirmed in that other church and you think that's enough for salvation.

33:06.962 --> 33:08.344
That has nothing to do with salvation.

33:10.747 --> 33:13.170
The only thing to do with salvation is do you believe in your heart

33:13.442 --> 33:16.206
and confess with your mouth the Lord Jesus Christ.

33:17.528 --> 33:19.951
And some of us say, well, I've prayed that prayer.

33:19.991 --> 33:21.413
I've been saved 30 times.

33:21.854 --> 33:24.397
No, there's no salvation without Lordship.

33:24.698 --> 33:28.443
The reason you say that is because you were never willing to make them Lord of your life.

33:28.703 --> 33:30.005
So then there's no salvation.

33:31.006 --> 33:31.767
Nothing changed.

33:31.787 --> 33:37.115
Yeah, because you have to, salvation is a byproduct of Lordship folks.

33:38.156 --> 33:40.039
We must ask them to be Lord of our life.

33:41.140 --> 33:42.322
You say, what does that mean?

33:42.594 --> 33:43.936
I don't have enough time to explain it.

33:43.976 --> 33:46.480
And I don't know if I can explain it fully other than to say this.

33:47.222 --> 33:48.664
He gets to lead and we follow.

33:49.505 --> 33:53.051
We get to come to His Word and say this, what the Word says, I'm a purpose to do it.

33:54.313 --> 33:57.619
And when we blow it, we repent to Him because we know we're accountable to Him.

33:58.080 --> 33:58.861
That's lordship.

